717693f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 99th Street
717693f-a.text:
2628 Broadway, east side, between 99th and 100th Streets.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 322.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
Neg W a1S

717694f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 99th Street
717694f-a.text:
(1)
Broadway, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of 99th Street. The
7lenham Apartment House, in the centre, will be demolished between
1930 and 1934, and replaced by a one-story theatre. The one-story
corner building will be replaced about the same time by the twenty-
story Trafalgar Tower Apartments.
July 27, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, showing also the south side of 99th Street from
Broadway to Amsterdam Avenue, with St. Michael's Protestant
Episcopal Church in the background.
July 27, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
